274
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:10,680
(Looking for a missing person)

275
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,000
Where's Dad?

276
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,800
Where is he?

277
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,520
Dad?

278
00:18:58,760 --> 00:18:59,800
Gosh.

279
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,360
I was planning to report you missing
if you didn't come home today.

280
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:06,080
-You were alive after all.
-I attended a seminar.

281
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:08,800
Stop lying, punk.

282
00:19:08,880 --> 00:19:11,760
I went on a trip since living is so tough.

283
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:14,560
What's so tough? Are you in agony?

284
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,120
Are you doing research?
Are you supporting a family?

285
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:20,120
If I'm ever born again,
I want to live like you.

286
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:22,040
I'm tired. I'm going to bed.

287
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:35,640
Hey. By the way...

288
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,760
-Don't talk to me.
-Mi-ran...

289
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:40,120
Is Mi-ran a girl whom
you're interested in lately?

290
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:44,680
I'm talking about Ko Mi-ran
who went to the US 20 years ago.

291
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,880
My first love, Ko Mi-ran.

292
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,440
"Ko Mi-ran"?

293
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,640
Your friend from college entrance
preparation school?

294
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,960
Yes, that Ko Mi-ran.

295
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:56,880
She hasn't contacted you
since then, right?

296
00:19:58,800 --> 00:19:59,880
No.

297
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:02,960
Why are you asking?

298
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,600
No reason.

299
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,200
I wonder if she made a family
and is living well over there.

300
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:08,560
You're so random.

301
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:09,840
Do you have nothing better to do

302
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:11,520
but to reminisce about your first love?

303
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:16,360
There's only so much my father can do

304
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,920
to prevent you from getting fired.

305
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,960
You should write dissertations
and go to seminars.

306
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:22,440
Show some effort, will you?
Stop living like a parasite.

307
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:23,880
What's the point of changing your name

308
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,880
when you're still a fool?

309
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:28,840
Did you call me a fool?

310
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:32,040
That's ridiculous.
You should talk more elegantly.

311
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:33,120
Why should I listen to you?

312
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,760
Why should I? Why should I?

313
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:40,760
Where did my life go wrong?

314
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,560
Both of us were ruined
because of Ko Mi-ran.

315
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:45,080
If you didn't make that mistake
after getting pathetically drunk

316
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,800
over Mi-ran...

317
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:50,280
Why do I bother?

318
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,320
I miss

319
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,680
Mi-ran.

320
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,720
Darn her.

321
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,720
Hey.

322
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:14,680
The moment the world finds out
that our station

323
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:18,320
kept quiet about Dong-chan going missing,

324
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,960
both of us will be fired.

325
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:23,160
We'll really be done for.
You know that, don't you?

326
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:26,520
Of course I do. What should we do now?

327
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,800
We have to pretend we don't know
anything until the end.

328
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:31,040
We covered up the mouths of every staff

329
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:32,720
who were involved in the experiment.

330
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,200
And the professor who worked
on the experiment is gone.

331
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,960
All we have to do is keep Dong-chan quiet.

332
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,800
Do you think it'll be easy
to keep him quiet?

333
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:44,760
That's what I'm worried about too.
He's crazy.

334
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,920
He's insane.

335
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:49,640
By the way, where did Ko Mi-ran go?

336
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,840
Whatever happened to her?

337
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:53,800
What's giving me the real headache is her.

338
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:57,320
She's worse than Dong-chan.
She's really crazy.

339
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,520
I mean it.

340
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,760
Don't tell me she's alive.

341
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:04,920
What are we going to do?
I knew this year was unlucky for me,

342
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,280
but this is driving me crazy.

343
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:09,360
I really don't feel like living.

344
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:12,400
Who on earth woke them up?

345
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:15,240
Where were they all this time anyway?

346
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,880
How is it possible

347
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:20,360
for him to look exactly the same?

348
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:23,000
What could've happened?

349
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,840
I'm speechless.

350
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:28,120
Is he really your older brother?

351
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:31,040
With all seriousness,
he looks like your son.

352
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,160
He strangely feels like someone else.

353
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,560
How is he different?

354
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:37,960
Compared to Dong-chan,

355
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,880
the back of his head looks different.

356
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,240
He has wider nostrils too.

357
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,720
His eyes look super cold, just like ice.

358
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:47,080
Doesn't he look extremely rude?

359
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:50,040
He was never nice.

360
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:53,160
Didn't he used to have a mole
under his left eye?

361
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,840
I couldn't see one earlier.

362
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:57,320
Why are you all talking nonsense?

363
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:01,000
If he isn't Dong-chan, then who is he?

364
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:04,800
When they investigated his phone,
they found a strange text.

365
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:07,600
It said, he would make sure
to succeed with the experiment.

366
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:10,560
He talked about "the experiment"
in several places.

367
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,720
Right.

368
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:15,200
I'm certain that Dong-chan
was involved in an experiment.

369
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:19,240
So? What kind of experiment
are you saying he did?

370
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,920
What are you thinking?

371
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,160
Clones.

372
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,760
She's right.

373
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:31,440
Anyway,

374
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:35,200
before Dong-chan talks to us first,

375
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,080
don't ask him anything.

376
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,160
Okay.

377
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,680
I'm sorry, Dad.

378
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:54,320
I couldn't send you on a cruise
like I promised.

379
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,280
I wasn't there
for your last moments either.

380
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,640
Dad...

381
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,440
Dad?

382
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:21,120
Dong-chan, what are you doing out here?

383
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,560
Aren't you going to bed?

384
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:26,640
Gosh. You surprised me.

385
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:28,880
I just...

386
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,480
What are you looking at?

387
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,000
Dad?

388
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,160
Dong-chan. Goodnight.

389
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:59,360
(When are you coming back, Mi-ran?)

390
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,400
Mi-ran.

391
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:17,640
(Mom cooked Mi-ran's favorite food.
She said Mi-ran's always with us.)

392
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:37,320
(Honey, when are you coming back?)

393
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:41,160
(Why aren't you coming?
I'm waiting for you.)

394
00:25:41,400 --> 00:25:44,720
(Honey, I'm waiting for you to come back.)

395
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,160
(Dong-chan.)

396
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:50,000
(I miss you.)

397
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:24,000
Do you feel okay?

398
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,480
We'll take you to the hospital

399
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,560
once you're done eating.

400
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:28,320
No, it's okay.

401
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:30,640
I feel so much better
now that I got some sleep.

402
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,200
Must you go back to school?

403
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:34,880
Why don't you get some more rest?

404
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,640
I rested for 20 years.

405
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,600
I should get back to my daily life.

406
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:41,960
We always had hope that you'd come back.

407
00:26:42,120 --> 00:26:45,800
So we filed for a leave of absence
every single year.

408
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,680
We've also kept your number alive.

409
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,440
But I came back a little late.

410
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:53,840
-Didn't I?
-Don't say that.

411
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,480
You didn't come back late.

412
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:57,680
My gosh, even if I end up

413
00:26:57,760 --> 00:27:00,400
dying tomorrow, I'd die a peaceful death.

414
00:27:00,480 --> 00:27:02,920
Why would you say something like that?

415
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:04,760
The new semester just started.

416
00:27:04,840 --> 00:27:06,440
And there's not much time
for me to achieve

417
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:08,000
everything I should've done
during the past 20 years.

418
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,880
I should live a diligent life.

419
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:12,760
I need to graduate and get a job.

420
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:13,920
Yes, you're right.

421
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,640
You can do everything you want.

422
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,400
But before that,

423
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:23,440
there's something I need to take care of.

424
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,840
Director Ma.

425
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:04,440
-I'm so glad you're...
-What in the world

426
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:05,720
happened here?

427
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,720
Professor Hwang got into an accident

428
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:10,040
two hours before the experiment
was supposed to end.

429
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:15,800
Then how were we able
to wake up in 20 years?

430
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,080
Was Professor Hwang

431
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,120
the person who woke us up?

432
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:00,520
Dissociative amnesia.

433
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,600
He woke up from a coma in 20 years.

434
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:06,680
And with his subconscious tenacity,
he woke you guys up

435
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:08,160
and lost consciousness again.

436
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:12,000
(You could say his body reacted
faster than his brain.)

437
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:15,600
(His subconsciousness that's been
dormant for 20 years)

438
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:17,320
(is what caused him to wake you up.)

439
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:19,640
(You could say it's similar)

440
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:21,760
(to a sleep disorder.)

441
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:27,960
They why does everyone think he's dead?

442
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,720
His car exploded.

443
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,600
(Someone tried to kill him.)

444
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:35,280
(If he found out that Professor Hwang
managed to stay alive,)

445
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:37,080
(he would've tried to kill him again.)

446
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,600
So we made it seem

447
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:41,240
like he was dead.

448
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,920
Professor Hwang and I went
to the same medical school.

449
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:47,320
(I don't know why,
but he was always nervous.)

450
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:50,920
(Right before the accident,
he called and desperately asked me)

451
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:54,440
(to handle everything
if anything bad happened to him.)

452
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,600
Did you find the culprit?

453
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:02,800
I guess we can't ask the cops

454
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:05,240
to investigate since the statute
of limitations has already expired.

455
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,800
I'm sure it has something to do
with the cryonics experiment.

456
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:10,480
We'll only be able to find out
once Professor Hwang wakes up.

457
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:12,360
I couldn't tell this to anyone

458
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:14,840
for the past 20 years

459
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,720
because I couldn't trust anyone.

460
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,200
Did you meet Ko Mi-ran?

461
00:30:33,280 --> 00:30:35,640
No, not yet.

462
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,560
Mi-ran's mother knew

463
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:39,880
that she was taking part
in the cryonics experiment.

464
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,120
I'm sorry.

465
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:44,240
I couldn't tell your parents

466
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:47,160
that you were participating
in the cryonics experiment.

467
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,000
I was worried that the experiment
might get exposed

468
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:50,760
and put Professor Hwang in grave danger.

469
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:54,800
I'm really sorry.

470
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,920
Hey.

471
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:19,360
Dong-chan, did you sleep well?

472
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,480
Ha-young.

473
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,360
I want to meet Ha-young.

474
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:28,800
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

475
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,920
-Good work, everyone.
-Thank you.

476
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:33,080
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

477
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:35,520
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

478
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:36,760
Thanks.

479
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,400
Hello?

480
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,480
Aren't you Na Ha-young, the news anchor?

481
00:32:24,840 --> 00:32:26,320
Can I get an autograph?

482
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,320
Thank you.

483
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:38,920
Dong-chan.

484
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:07,760
Have you been well?

485
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,760
It's been 20 years already.

486
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:13,280
Yes, I know.

487
00:34:17,320 --> 00:34:19,600
I'm really late, aren't I?

488
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:23,280
I should've listened to you
and gave up on the experiment

489
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:26,320
had I known that this was going to happen.

490
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,920
It's all in the past.

491
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,880
I already forgot about it all.

492
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:35,159
I'm sorry.

493
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:40,840
I couldn't keep my promise.

494
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:45,560
What did I tell you?

495
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,800
I told you not to do the experiment.

496
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:53,239
Why did you do that? Why?

497
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,440
You told me that you won't regret it.

498
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,520
But look what happened!

499
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:06,120
I'm sorry.

500
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:08,680
But I am

501
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:13,440
thankful that you are

502
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:20,960
still alive.

503
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:32,560
I have to go back to work.

504
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:34,520
I'll call you later.

505
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:49,440
Is there no way of resolving
hypothermia of the two people

506
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:51,160
who woke up?

507
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,320
Nothing for now.

508
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:04,320
During the first experiment,
the dolphin died

509
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,320
because we couldn't resolve
the problem of hypothermia.

510
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:10,280
Professor Hwang researched for years
to resolve this problem.

511
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:13,840
And in the end, he created
a medicine that returns

512
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:15,760
the body temperature to normal.

513
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,800
Professor Hwang is the only one
who could bring back

514
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:21,680
the two frozen people to life.

515
00:37:24,640 --> 00:37:26,680
That means
if Professor Hwang doesn't wake up,

516
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:29,560
the two of them will remain in danger.

517
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:31,360
(Promissory note)

518
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:45,520
Is she

519
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:47,120
Ko Mi-ran?

520
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,360
Oh, no.

521
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,040
That's Ma Dong-chan. It's definitely him.

522
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:44,640
Mi-ran.

523
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,960
I looked everywhere for you.
Are you all...

524
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:54,120
What are you...

525
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:00,600
Give me back my 20 years.

526
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:05,000
Give me back my life that you took away!

527
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,880
-What's going on?
-Who is that?

528
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,360
Let's talk somewhere else.

529
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,000
Cut! Okay.

530
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,040
We're rehearsing.

531
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,600
Go on, everyone. Get moving.

532
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,240
Cameras, come on out.

533
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,520
Isn't she that woman

534
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:46,440
who took part in that experiment
with Dong-chan?

535
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:47,520
What?

536
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:50,200
Yes.

537
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:57,360
Explain yourself. How can this happen?

538
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:58,840
Twenty years?

539
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:02,640
Wait, did you say it's only
for a day when it was 20 years?

540
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,360
What are you talking about?

541
00:41:04,760 --> 00:41:06,760
